  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lebanese Red Cross Appeal - Beirut Blast</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the 4th of August Beirut Port explosion tragedy, the Lebanese Red Cross is providing direct unconditional cash assistance ($300, in USD) to at least 10,000 families for a period of 7 months. This modality is helping the most vulnerable affected families to choose and address their own priority needs.  With 316,000 USD, LRC will be able to support 1000 families for one month, with each family receiving the full 300 USD. 16,000 USD will be used for banking and operational fees.</narrative>
  </description>
